 </row>
</tbody>



</tgroup>
</table><table id="eip-id1168467276065" class="unnumbered unstyled" summary="."><label/>
<tgroup cols="2"><tbody>
 <row>
 <entry><span class="token">ⓒ</span> </entry>
 <entry/>
 </row>
 <row>
 <entry>The graph crosses the <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>-axis at the point (−5, 0).</entry>
 <entry>The <emphasis effect="italics">x</emphasis>-intercept is (−5, 0).</entry>
 </row>
 <row>
  <entry>The graph crosses the <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-axis at the point (0, −5).</entry>
 <entry>The <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis>-intercept is (0, −5).</entry>
 </row>
</tbody>




</tgroup>
</table></solution></exercise></example><note id="fs-id1655344" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1355420">
<problem id="fs-id1513871">
<para id="fs-id1350723">Find the <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mtext>-</m:mtext></m:math> and <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mtext>-intercepts</m:mtext></m:math> of the graph: <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:math></para>
