<para id="fs-id1829802"><emphasis effect="bold">Road trip</emphasis> Ozzie filled up the gas tank of his truck and went on a road trip. The <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mtext>-axis</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> on the graph shows the number of miles Ozzie drove since filling up. The <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mtext>-axis</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math> represents the number of gallons of gas in the truck’s gas tank.</para><media id="fs-id1829825" alt="The graph shows the x y-coordinate plane. The x and y-axis each run from - to .  A line passes through labeled points “ordered pair 0, 16” and “ordered pair 300, 0”.">
